      "content": "see i knew it wouldn't just be me. it's not just \"unsettling\" though. it feels deliberate. like, why would a major retailer use this specific frequency of lines and colors in their \"basic\" lines? it feels like they're using psychological triggers to keep people from being too disruptive or questioning things. do you think corporations actually use sub-perceptual design tricks like that for social engineering?",
